      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_1_listing_1",
      "firm_id": "sybil_1",
      "description": "Hey there! I\u2019m selling my absolute pride and joy. Honestly, this car has been babied since day one and looks like it just rolled off the showroom floor! It's in truly flawless condition\u2014no scratches, no dents, and the interior still has that fresh feel. It drives like a dream and has been kept in a climate-controlled garage. I'm sad to see it go, but I know the next owner is going to have a blast with it. Feel free to reach out if you want to come see it in person!",
      "price": 45500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This E46 M3 is a superlative example of BMW M-Division engineering, featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. The powerplant utilizes individual throttle bodies and a recalibrated double-VANOS system for razor-sharp throttle response. Mated to a precise Getrag six-speed manual gearbox, the drivetrain delivers power through a variable M differential lock with zero lash. Critical mechanical points have been addressed: the rear subframe has been structurally reinforced, and the rod bearings have been replaced with documented clearances. The suspension retains its factory-correct damping characteristics with no bushing compliance issues. This vehicle is in collector-grade condition, boasting original paint thickness and an interior free of bolster wear or pixel degradation in the cluster.",
      "price": 46500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 5
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_3_listing_3",
      "firm_id": "sybil_3",
      "description": "Mint condition. Garage kept. Clean title. No mechanical issues. Original paint. Full service history included.",
      "price": 43500.0,
